<br>
I dont know about anyone else.  I do not want to see FoT become nonvendor NOW. Its too late already. That genie is out of the bottle, so to speak, making it a drop spell now accomplishes nothing but nerfing the few who were not smart enough to port to Knowledge and buy it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Your estimation of 10% of wizards having EER and/or GSS is WAY over though.  If 5% of wizards have GSS, I would guess that is a lot.  Right now on my server, there are maybe a dozen or so (all from the top guild) that have GSS. <br>
<br>
EER is a little more common, but still not at that 10% number.  <br>
<br>
Drop rates, it sounds to me, have been a mess for some time and continue to be.  <br>
<br>
Keep FoT where it is, changing it now does nothing but for G-D's sake, make some of the wizard nukes available. <p>Garrath Moore &lt;BR&gt;<br>
